John’s project started on January 15, 2021, and the team is expected to complete the first phase by March 5, 2022. His manager, Sarah, requested that all progress reports be submitted on a monthly basis, with the first one due on February 1, 2022. The second phase is scheduled to begin on April 10, 2022, with the final project wrap-up slated for December 31, 2022.

In addition, Sarah mentioned during the meeting on 03/15/2022 that they would be holding a review session every quarter. She emphasized that the first session should occur no later than 04/30/2022. As of today, October 20, 2024, the team has made significant progress. John and his team had their first review on May 1, 2022, and the second review took place on August 2, 2022. The third review session is scheduled for November 5, 2022. Sarah mentioned that the final review will occur on 12/15/2022, and all final deliverables should be submitted by that date.

Outside of work, John planned his vacation from June 15, 2022, to June 30, 2022. He also has a family event coming up on 07/25/2022, and a wedding to attend on July 27, 2022. He’s scheduled to attend a conference on September 14, 2022, and another on September 29, 2022. His daughter’s birthday is on 10/20/2024, which happens to coincide with a major project deadline.

Reflecting on past events, John remembers that the initial proposal for this project was submitted on 01/10/2021, and the first meeting with stakeholders occurred on 01/25/2021. He’s been looking forward to wrapping up everything by the end of 2024.